1
00:00:08,510 --> 00:00:09,190
Come in.

2
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:14,400
Wear these slippers.

3
00:00:15,350 --> 00:00:16,120
Frying Pan.

4
00:00:17,670 --> 00:00:18,440
Frying Pan.

5
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:20,920
Where did it go?

6
00:00:22,230 --> 00:00:23,670
Normally, it's not afraid of strangers.

7
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:25,870
Why is it afraid of you?

8
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:28,390
Frying Pan.

9
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:30,960
Where could it be?

10
00:00:43,110 --> 00:00:44,960
You're crawling under the sofa again,

11
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:46,430
getting yourself covered in dirt,

12
00:00:46,710 --> 00:00:48,000
and you come into my bed.

13
00:00:51,560 --> 00:00:52,390
Stay here for a bit.

14
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:00,240
Take this.

15
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:02,280
Check if it's expired.

16
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:03,560
I'll go and make some food.

17
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:04,840
I'll say this in advance.

18
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:05,920
I don't serve young masters.

19
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:07,040
You'll eat whatever I cook.

20
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:08,280
Don't be picky.

21
00:02:25,470 --> 00:02:28,560
♪Happy birthday to you♪

22
00:02:28,870 --> 00:02:31,800
♪Happy birthday to you♪

23
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,520
♪Happy birthday to you♪

24
00:02:40,430 --> 00:02:41,150
Pei Su,

25
00:02:41,430 --> 00:02:42,400
what's the matter?

26
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:44,120
Look at this.

27
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,190
What's this?

28
00:02:47,150 --> 00:02:48,520
He tore the first few pages.

29
00:02:48,870 --> 00:02:50,000
I traced it with a pencil.

30
00:02:50,310 --> 00:02:51,470
It's his dad's whereabouts.

31
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:54,430
This kid was tailing his dad.

32
00:03:02,310 --> 00:03:03,030
Pei Su!

33
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,030
Pei Su!

34
00:03:33,870 --> 00:03:36,310
♪Happy birthday to...♪

35
00:03:45,710 --> 00:03:47,150
What are you looking at?

36
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,030
I don't know how to sing the birthday song.

37
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,120
Are you planning to make a wish?

38
00:03:56,030 --> 00:03:58,630
You can wish not to get hit
by a car on your next birthday.

39
00:04:30,430 --> 00:04:31,040
Here.

40
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:33,240
The doctor said drinking milk is good.

41
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:40,920
So another year has gone.

42
00:04:41,430 --> 00:04:42,720
I hate nagging at you.

43
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,120
But find something proper to do.

44
00:04:44,390 --> 00:04:45,950
How long are you going to live like this?

45
00:04:48,390 --> 00:04:50,480
The result of a vast wealth of material life

46
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:52,390
tends to motivate people to strive for more

47
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,720
than become complacent and idle.

48
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:57,390
A young person can't live without any goals.

49
00:04:58,390 --> 00:04:59,680
You will get yourself into trouble one day.

50
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:05,160
This is what human nature is.

51
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,680
First, they pursue basic needs
like food and shelter.

52
00:05:07,310 --> 00:05:08,600
When they've accomplished those

53
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,800
and started feeling comfortable,

54
00:05:10,070 --> 00:05:12,040
they're bound
to seek higher levels of satisfaction.

55
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,510
For example, a sense of accomplishment
and self-actualization

56
00:05:14,510 --> 00:05:16,360
while indulging in frivolous spending.

57
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:18,120
That's a form of escapism.

58
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:19,070
In the long run,

59
00:05:19,070 --> 00:05:21,600
the hidden anxiety will be tormenting.

60
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:23,390
They'll buy a house today

61
00:05:23,510 --> 00:05:24,600
and a car tomorrow.

62
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,830
Can these relieve the pain

63
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:28,160
of conflicting human nature?

64
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:29,070
The pain of not being able to afford it

65
00:05:29,070 --> 00:05:30,310
is obviously more surface-level.

66
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:36,390
I'm giving you advice as an elder.

67
00:05:36,390 --> 00:05:37,720
Yet, you talked back.

68
00:05:38,510 --> 00:05:39,510
If you grew up in my family

69
00:05:39,510 --> 00:05:40,830
acting like a little rascal,

70
00:05:40,830 --> 00:05:42,000
you would've already dragged a stool

71
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,360
to the door and started writing
your self-reflection.

72
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:44,560
You wouldn't have been able to eat at all.

73
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,870
My family usually doesn't talk over meals.

74
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,270
Unless we had guests around.

75
00:05:58,870 --> 00:06:00,800
Or else I wouldn't see my dad
at the dinner table often.

76
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:03,830
My mom was emotionally unstable,

77
00:06:04,430 --> 00:06:06,000
and she would act out for no reason.

78
00:06:07,390 --> 00:06:09,510
Sometimes, she would just
put down her utensils and leave

79
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,630
or start sobbing at the dinner table
out of a sudden.

80
00:06:15,950 --> 00:06:17,160
I always feel anxious

81
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:18,390
eating at the dinner table at home.

82
00:06:19,190 --> 00:06:20,310
Having it peacefully once in a while

83
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,310
was like hitting the jackpot.

84
00:06:29,510 --> 00:06:30,920
That sounds pretty miserable.

85
00:06:32,430 --> 00:06:34,160
But compared to writing a self-reflection,

86
00:06:34,510 --> 00:06:35,750
which is more comfortable?

87
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:39,830
I'm serious.

88
00:06:40,830 --> 00:06:41,750
Think about this.

89
00:06:42,430 --> 00:06:43,560
You get a stool

90
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:44,750
and lean against the door

91
00:06:45,390 --> 00:06:46,600
with a piece of paper

92
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,510
as you face the neighbor's main entrance.

93
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,600
In the summer,

94
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,950
people would only close the security door.

95
00:06:50,950 --> 00:06:52,830
So anyone outside could see
what you were doing inside.

96
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,750
And the neighbors
would be your parents' co-workers.

97
00:06:54,870 --> 00:06:56,560
Anyone who passed by would ask,

98
00:06:56,830 --> 00:06:57,560
"Hey, kiddo.

99
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,870
What did you do wrong this time?"

100
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:02,750
It's a grave insult to one's character and dignity.

101
00:07:07,970 --> 00:07:08,950
[Feiling Alert]

102
00:07:14,510 --> 00:07:15,270
Yes, Tao Ze.

103
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:16,000
Luo.

104
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:16,680
What's up?

105
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:17,750
Tang Ning was here.

106
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,560
Chen is missing.

107
00:08:46,670 --> 00:08:50,070
[Justice in the Dark]

108
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:53,150
[Episode 8]

109
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:54,670
Please.

110
00:08:54,670 --> 00:08:56,000
Can you try and recall

111
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,600
and see if you miss any detail?

112
00:08:57,630 --> 00:08:59,120
We'll definitely find Chen.

113
00:09:08,630 --> 00:09:09,320
Captain Luo.

114
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,390
Have you taken the parents' statement yet?

115
00:09:10,390 --> 00:09:11,150
Yes.

116
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:13,510
Mr. Pei,

117
00:09:13,510 --> 00:09:15,720
what happened to your arm?

118
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:16,480
A minor accident.

119
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:18,960
They said they enrolled Chen

120
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:20,080
in a painting class here for the summer break.

121
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,440
Her parents would be the ones who pick her up.

122
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:22,480
But her dad had to work overtime today

123
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:23,790
and came one hour late.

124
00:09:23,790 --> 00:09:25,360
When he arrived, he couldn't find her anywhere.

125
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,240
This place was renovated early this year.

126
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,320
The teacher-in-charge

127
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,120
said there are no blind spots

128
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,480
in the current surveillance system.

129
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:35,150
Before Mr. Tao went out,
he had sent someone to investigate it.

130
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:41,270
Move it!

131
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:42,840
What is this?

132
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:45,600
The forensic team tracked down Chen's phone.

133
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,840
So I led the men over right away.

134
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:48,000
And we caught this guy

135
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,080
on Street No. 15,

136
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:50,030
a habitual offender.

137
00:09:50,550 --> 00:09:51,600
There should be a special place

138
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,840
where they could sell stolen goods
on that street.

139
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:54,720
I've sent the Patrol Detachment to take over.

140
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:55,630
What about Chen?

141
00:09:57,030 --> 00:09:58,080
This guy said

142
00:09:58,150 --> 00:09:59,200
he saw a little girl

143
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,440
tying her shoelace on the road.

144
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,600
She put the phone on the flower bed beside her.

145
00:10:02,630 --> 00:10:04,030
She left after she tied her shoelace

146
00:10:04,030 --> 00:10:05,080
and forgot her phone.

147
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,080
So he picked it up.

148
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:07,200
Which street?

149
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,200
When did he pick it up?

150
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:10,030
It should be around XWI Children's Palace.

151
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,390
We found eight phones on him.

152
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:14,270
He was preparing

153
00:10:14,270 --> 00:10:15,630
to sell his spoils for the day.

154
00:10:16,030 --> 00:10:16,670
Take him back to the station.

155
00:10:16,670 --> 00:10:17,720
-Come with us.
-Go.

156
00:10:17,870 --> 00:10:19,320
This rascal doesn't know

157
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,390
the specific time and place.

158
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,240
It's only a minor injury.

159
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:25,910
Don't mind me.

160
00:10:26,030 --> 00:10:26,630
Ze,

161
00:10:26,910 --> 00:10:28,200
you don't look too good.

162
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:33,240
I asked Tang Ning.

163
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:36,600
Chen wore a floral dress

164
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:40,360
before she went missing.

165
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:46,320
If it's true,

166
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:48,670
the perpetrator's frequency

167
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:50,440
of abducting two girls

168
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:51,390
within five days is too high.

169
00:10:51,390 --> 00:10:52,960
Qu Tong is likely...

170
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,000
Chen was kidnapped before 5 PM.

171
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:04,200
It's been more than seven hours since then.

172
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,200
It's also likely...

173
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:09,320
Mr. Tao. Captain Luo.

174
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:10,720
We found the girl
from the school's surveillance camera.

175
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:12,360
Tao Ze,

176
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:13,440
leave this to me.

177
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,550
Talk to the parents

178
00:11:15,910 --> 00:11:17,670
to see if the child
has had unusual behavior recently.

179
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:19,240
You should also ask if they have offended anyone

180
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:20,320
or how they get along with the child.

181
00:11:21,030 --> 00:11:22,440
Don't overlook any possible factors.

182
00:11:23,030 --> 00:11:24,440
Do you need my help?

183
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,750
Oh, you've met the suspect.

184
00:11:28,030 --> 00:11:28,630
Zhang,

185
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:30,840
take him to the station
for a facial composite of the suspect

186
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:32,840
and let him analyze criminal psychology.

187
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:33,150
Yes, sir.

188
00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:34,080
Let's go to the Monitoring Room.

189
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:34,840
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

190
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:35,320
Where is it?

191
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:36,440
I'll lead you the way.

192
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:37,320
Mr. Pei, come with me.

193
00:11:38,050 --> 00:11:42,050
[XWI Children's Palace]

194
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,080
What was she looking at?

195
00:12:09,510 --> 00:12:10,480
Was there someone outside the window?

196
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:16,630
Mirror.

197
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,790
She used the window as a mirror.

198
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:21,510
She only needed to turn her head
to look at the view.

199
00:12:21,510 --> 00:12:23,080
She didn't have to turn her whole body

200
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:24,080
to get a closer look.

201
00:12:25,150 --> 00:12:26,870
She also played with her hair
using a ballpoint pen.

202
00:12:26,870 --> 00:12:27,960
All girls know what this means.

203
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:43,000
Pause it.

204
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:47,000
What is the location across the window
that Chen was looking at?

205
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:48,870
Playground.

206
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:49,750
Get the surveillance footage

207
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:51,510
of the playground before

208
00:12:51,510 --> 00:12:52,440
and after 5:12 PM.

209
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:14,600
What's this?

210
00:13:15,630 --> 00:13:17,000
Didn't you say your surveillance camera
covers every corner of the park?

211
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:17,600
It's not that.

212
00:13:17,790 --> 00:13:20,320
The red row in the northwest corner
is a public toilet.

213
00:13:20,870 --> 00:13:22,080
There's no surveillance camera there.

214
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:23,320
What else is there except for the public toilet?

215
00:13:26,030 --> 00:13:26,720
Tell us now.

216
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:37,630
This is the place.

217
00:13:38,670 --> 00:13:40,720
It was left from the repair of the playground.

218
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,910
No one repaired this fence,

219
00:13:42,910 --> 00:13:45,030
so a hole was left behind.

220
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:46,910
Where does this lead to?

221
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:50,120
A small park.

222
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:50,910
It's not big.

223
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,510
No one goes deep into the park.

224
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:54,630
Are you planning to head inside?

225
00:13:55,910 --> 00:13:57,480
Tell our men to search the park.

226
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:58,080
Yes, sir.

227
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:01,270
Do I need to bring them inside?

228
00:14:01,270 --> 00:14:02,030
It's okay.

229
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:04,270
I need to talk to all the kids

230
00:14:04,270 --> 00:14:05,670
in the footage.

231
00:14:05,670 --> 00:14:06,750
Please follow our men

232
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:08,200
to contact their parents as soon as possible.

233
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:08,910
Okay.

234
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:18,440
-Captain Luo.
-Yes.

235
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:19,720
Where's Xu Dongyu?

236
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:20,720
At home.

237
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,550
He made a copy of the dashcam for Mr. Tao.

238
00:14:22,550 --> 00:14:23,750
After we left,

239
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:25,150
he drove to a restaurant

240
00:14:25,150 --> 00:14:26,720
for a takeaway. He didn't go anywhere
after he reached home.

241
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:28,080
Are you sure he's at home?

242
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:28,750
Yes.

243
00:14:28,790 --> 00:14:29,720
He didn't draw his curtain.

244
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:30,910
He has been in the living room.

245
00:14:30,910 --> 00:14:32,240
He was never away from our sight.

246
00:14:32,510 --> 00:14:33,240
What's wrong, sir?

247
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:33,870
Nothing.

248
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,150
Keep watching him.

249
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:36,360
Don't make any mistakes.

250
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:38,600
Captain Luo,

251
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,720
did we suspect the wrong person?

252
00:14:42,910 --> 00:14:44,720
Wu said Xu Dongyu

253
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:46,150
didn't draw the curtain after he reached home.

254
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:48,510
It's already dawn, but he didn't draw the curtain.

255
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:49,960
So he's very certain

256
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:51,440
that Xu Dongyu is at home.

257
00:14:51,510 --> 00:14:52,910
But don't you think it's weird?

258
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:55,080
The person being watched

259
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,670
is very cooperative.

260
00:14:57,270 --> 00:14:58,200
Logically,

261
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,910
the more perfect and reasonable it is,

262
00:15:00,150 --> 00:15:01,120
the more suspicious it is

263
00:15:01,390 --> 00:15:02,600
in reality.

264
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:05,600
I need to go in and check things out.

265
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:06,440
Stay here.

266
00:15:06,550 --> 00:15:07,630
When you got into contact with the kids,

267
00:15:07,630 --> 00:15:08,270
call me.

268
00:15:08,270 --> 00:15:08,870
Yes, sir.

269
00:15:23,870 --> 00:15:24,720
It was my fault.

270
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:27,320
Why didn't I even think of checking it myself?

271
00:15:32,870 --> 00:15:33,550
Mr. Zhang,

272
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:36,510
it's said that the child tracking system
on the mobile phone

273
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:37,790
can switch on and off remotely.

274
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:38,510
The SID

275
00:15:38,510 --> 00:15:39,600
should have traced Chen's phone

276
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:40,870
using this way just now.

277
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:42,670
Why didn't you think

278
00:15:42,670 --> 00:15:44,200
about switching it on remotely just now?

279
00:15:44,270 --> 00:15:45,360
I tried.

280
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:47,240
But I don't know what happened

281
00:15:47,240 --> 00:15:48,270
to the application.

282
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:50,150
It kept showing

283
00:15:50,150 --> 00:15:51,750
connection failure again and again.

284
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:53,870
